Let's now calculate the future value of selling the asset.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present value} &=\dfrac{\$ 145,000 
}{\left(1 + 0.11\right)^{4}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$ 145,000}{1.51807041}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$95,516}
\end{aligned}$$

Based on our calculation, the future value of selling the sale of asset is $95,516.

Next, to determine if the firm will profit in selling the asset, we will subtract the cost of acquiring the asset to the present value of selling the asset from the previous step. Hence, we will use the following formula:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Profit} &= \text{Present Value of Sales}-\text{Cost of Acquisition}

\end{aligned}$$
